                <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/1010: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-17T10:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 17, 1922—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. My telegram number 68, August 12, 10 a.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d244fn30">Not
                        printed.</note> Senate and Chamber of Deputies have given practically
                    unanimous vote of confidence to Minister for Foreign Affairs for his conduct of
                    negotiations in Washington. Early ratification probable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sterling</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
